nl.tno.stormcv.operation

Class FramesToVideoOp

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tno.stormcv.operation.FramesToVideoOp
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, IBatchOperation<CVParticle>, IOperation<CVParticle>

    public class FramesToVideoOp
extends Object
implements IBatchOperation<CVParticle>
    A BatchOperation that creates video files or VideoChunk objects out of the frames it receives. The framesPerVideo parameter defines how big the video's will be. This operation has two modes; writes Frame's to a set of video files with name 'streamId_index.mp4' using h264 encoding. The index starts at 0 and is increased with 1 for
    • output VideoChunk objects: the video's generated will be send to the next bolt in the topology. Video will be encoded using the specified codec and put in a wmv container. Video objects can be converted back into either Frame or GroupOfFrames using the VideoToFramesOp. This used less bandwidth than sending the frames individually (raw). The actual bytesize of video chunks can be minimized by setting a high speed (also depends on framerate)
    • write video files to the specified (remote) location and sent the original Frames it gets to the next bolt in the topology. Each file has an index value, starting at 0, which is incremented for each file written.
    The number of frames that have to be written to each individual video chunk must be specified upon construction of this class. By default the video's have normal speed but this can be changed by specifying a speed factor. Example: a stream is read by a spout and 1 frame every second is emitted into the topology. A StreamWriterOp configured to put 60 frames in a file and a speed factor of 2.0 will create video's of 30 seconds long (running at twice the normal speed). It is possible to specify additional parameters like bitrate and ffmpeg parameters to tune the speed and quality.
    Author:
    Corne Versloot

        public FramesToVideoOp(String location,
                       long framesPerVideo)
        Constructs a writer that will put files in the provided location (must be a directory!). Each video will contain at last framesPerFile number of frames.
        Parameters:
        location - the directory where video's must be written to (can be a remote location like ftp if there is a FileConnector present)
        framesPerVideo - minimum number of frames put in a single file

      • FramesToVideoOp

        public FramesToVideoOp(long framesPerFile)
        Constructs a writer that will generate VideoChunk objects from frames it receives. Each video will contain at last framesPerFile number of frames. By default the WMV2 codec within a wmv container is used because this combination avoids framelos due to Xuggler/ffmpeg holding frames in buffers.
        Parameters:
        framesPerFile - minimum number of frames put in a single file
